==English==

===Noun===
# A heavy [[canvas]].
====Etymology====
[[Old English]] [[pæll]] "altar cloth, cloak, covering", from [[Latin]] [[pallium]] "cloak, covering".

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔːl|-ɔːl]]

===Verb===
'''to pall'''

#To make [[vapid]] or [[insipid]]; to make lifeless or spiritless; to dull; to weaken.
====Etymology====
''become tiresome'' attested [[w:1700|1700]], from [[Middle English]] [[pallen]] ''to grow feeble'' first attested [[w:1390|1390]], aphetic form of [[appallen]] ''to grow faint'' (see [[appal]]).
